amily.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Her mother did not approve of her friendship with Ahmed.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">How can you let such a silly incident ruin your friendship?</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">It was a period of her life when she made some lifelong friendships.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">It will be a pleasure to renew our friendship.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Their affair had started out as an innocent friendship.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Their quarrel meant the end of a beautiful friendship.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">friendships formed while she was at college</span></li></ul></span></div><span class=\"topic-g\"><span class=\"prefix\">Topics </span><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/family-and-relationships?level=b1\" title=\"Topic family-and-relationships\"><span class=\"topic\" href=\"l2:people:family_and_relationships?cefr=b1\"><span class=\"topic_name\">Family and relationships</span><span class=\"topic_cefr\">b1</span></span></a></span><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"snippet\" id=\"friendship_unbox_2\"><span class=\"box_title\">Oxford Collocations Dictionary</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"unbox\">adjective</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">deep</li><li class=\"li\">firm</li><li class=\"li\">good</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">verb + friendship</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">build</li><li class=\"li\">develop</li><li class=\"li\">establish</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">friendship + verb</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">develop</li><li class=\"li\">grow</li><li class=\"li\">begin</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">pr